<title>USA: Tridex expects profit post TransAct spinoff.</title>
<headline>Tridex expects profit post TransAct spinoff.</headline>
<dateline>WESTPORT, Conn. 1996-08-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tridex said it expects to be profitable on annual revenue of about $35 million after the planned spin-off of its TransAct Technologies Inc unit.</p>
<p>Tridex said the spinoff will be accomplished in early 1997 by distributing TransAct stock to Tridex shareholders.</p>
<p>After the distribution, Tridex said it will be comprised of its Cash Bases GB Ltd and Ultimate Technology Corp subsidiaries, which together are expected to be profitable on annualized revenue of about $35 million.</p>
<p>-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.</p>
</text>
